          "text": "# AGENTS.md instructions for /Users/jserv/playground/cortexm-linux\n\n<INSTRUCTIONS>\n# AGENTS.md\n\nThis file provides guidance to coding agents working in this repository.\n\n## Project\n\nMinimal build system for Linux on ARM Cortex-M4 (nommu). A single shell script\n(`build.sh`) produces a cross-toolchain, uClibc-ng, BusyBox userspace, Linux\nkernel with initramfs, and an ARM boot wrapper targeting MPS2-AN386 under QEMU.\n\n## Build and Run\n\nThis is a Linux-only project. All build and run commands MUST be executed on\n`node1` via `ssh node1`.\n\n```sh\nssh node1\ncd ~/playground/cortexm-linux/\n\n./build.sh            # full build (downloads sources automatically)\n./build.sh clean      # remove build artifacts (keeps downloads/)\n\nqemu-system-arm -M mps2-an386 -cpu cortex-m4 -nographic -kernel bootwrapper/linux.axf\n# exit QEMU: Ctrl-a x\n```\n\nThere is no incremental build. Re-running after a failure resumes roughly where\nit stopped.\n\nBuild order: binutils -> GCC (C only, first-pass) -> Linux headers ->\nuClibc-ng -> elf2flt -> BusyBox -> rootfs -> kernel (embedded initramfs) ->\nboot wrapper.\n\n## Key Constraints\n\n- Cortex-M4 is nommu/Thumb-2 only (ARMv7E-M). Binaries use FLAT format\n  (elf2flt), not ELF.\n- The reversed binutils patch (`patch -p1 -R`) prevents ARM-mode stub insertion\n  on Thumb-only targets.\n- QEMU MPS2-AN386 has no kernel loader; the boot wrapper, cloned from\n  ARM-software/bootwrapper on the `cortex-m-linux` branch, provides reset\n  vectors and boots the kernel at `0x21000000`.\n\n## Layout\n\n- `configs/` -- `.config` files for BusyBox/uClibc-ng, `rootfs.dev` device table\n- `patches/` -- binutils linker patch, applied in reverse\n- `downloads/`, `toolchain/`, `rootfs/`, `bootwrapper/` -- generated at build time\n\n## Version Bumps\n\nUpdate `*_VERSION` and `*_URL` in `build.sh`, and add matching configs in\n`configs/` using the `<pkg>-<version>[-<flavor>].config` naming pattern.\n\n## Git Policy\n\nNever